<item>
            <title>[HBASE-13610] Backport HBASE-13222 (Provide means of non-destructive balancer inspection) to 0.98</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-13610</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We have an internal user who wanted a facility like this during a recent upgrade.&lt;br/&gt;
On &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-13222&quot; title=&quot;Provide means of non-destructive balancer inspection&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-13222&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-13222&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=elserj&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;elserj&quot;&gt;Josh Elser&lt;/a&gt; said:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve dropped 0.98 from the fixVersions since the patch ended up being much more intrusive than Nicks initial patch.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I skimmed the V3 patch (&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/attachment/12707615/HBASE-13222-v3.patch&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/attachment/12707615/HBASE-13222-v3.patch&lt;/a&gt;) and the essential change is an Admin API addition &lt;tt&gt;public boolean isBalancerOn()&lt;/tt&gt;, and a new shell command, both of which we can do in 0.98 minors. Going to port back those parts.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
